Jurgen Klopp did have other options in Sepp van den Berg and Nathaniel Phillips but he wanted to reward Rhys Williams for what he had witnessed on the training field at Melwood. He had earned his opportunity and he didn&rsquo;t disappoint. #awlfc [@JamesPearceLFC]<br />
<br />
Klopp: &ldquo;Rhys was exceptional. The boy showed up in training. He will be a proper leader. It was his first game but I could hear him out on that pitch which was really good. He didn&rsquo;t struggle and looked really capable in all the situations he faced.&rdquo;
